added.title: TV Knight 4
added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon go camping but instead of fun outdoor activities they'd rather watch TV.

added.title: TV Knight 5
added.description: Batman pretends to be sick to avoid work so he and Commissioner Gordon can run around town watching their favorite shows.

added.title: TV Knight
added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon check in on various happenings around Jump City.

added.title: TV Knight 2
added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon have a slumber party and watch their favorite TV shows.

added.title: TV Knight 3
added.description: Batman is more interested in watching TV than participating in his birthday party.

added.title: The Inquisition
added.description: The students of Elmore Junior High find their world turned upside down when the mysterious school superintendent comes to stamp out their cartoonish ways. But who wants to be normal? Certainly not Gumball and Darwin.

added.title: Doorway to Helen
added.description: Craig makes a long distance connection with a kid that loves the creek as much as he does.

added.title: The Last Kid in the Creek
added.description: A terrible curse leaves Craig as the only kid in the creek.

added.title: The Climb
added.description: Craig's phone gets stuck in Mt. Sycamore, the tallest tree in the creek!

added.title: The Kid From 3030
added.description: The kids meet a mysterious kid from the future and try to help him complete his mission.

added.title: Falafel's Passion
added.description: Apple and Onion try to help Falafel find his passion but it looks like things might take a humiliating turn.

added.title: Our Stuff
added.description: After the bears play a little pickup basketball (they're very bad), they go back to grab their stuff by the side of the court only to find it's been stolen!  The Bears race across town trying to track down their stuff and end up cracking a giant case in the process.

added.title: Viral Video
added.description: The Bears think they have what it takes to make and star in a viral video, but when Nom-Nom decides that they don't, Grizz breaks into the koala's limo in an effort to change his mind.

added.title: Charlie and the Snake
added.description: Charlie is a solo guy who, like the Bears, would love to find a place for himself in the world. In an effort to do so, Charlie throws a party, but ends up going on an adventure with the unlikeliest of animals, a wild snake.

added.title: Speed Demon/Mojo Jonesin'
added.description: Mojo Jonesin':  When the children of Pokey Oaks become envious of the girls' superpowers, a mysterious figure offers them Chemical X. Now, the girls must fight their own classmates who have powers equal to their own./Speed Demon: The girls accidentally fly at the speed of light and when they arrive home, everything has changed. Fifty years have passed and the world has been taken over by Him.

added.title: Escape from Monster Island
added.description: After Bubbles wins two tickets to see the girls' favorite band Sensitive Thugz, Blossom and Buttercup vie for her plus one. But when the Mayor's plane crashes on Monster Island, the girls must put aside their differences to save the day!

added.title: Bye Bye, Bellum
added.description: The Mayor becomes dependent on the Powerpuff Girls after his assistant Ms. Bellum departs, leaving the girls so busy they accidentally hire the dangerous Bianca Bikini as his new assistant! When Bianca captures the Powerpuff Girls, the Mayor finds the tables turned and must rely on himself to help them.

added.title: Tiara Trouble
added.description: Bubbles' excitement over being a contestant in the Townsville Beauty, Talent and All-Around Flair pageant is ruined when Blossom and Buttercup become overbearing stage-sisters. But when a mysterious tiara causes trouble for the contestants, they realize there are bigger problems at hand.

added.title: Blank Eyed Girl
added.description: One very spooky night, Finn and Jake come face-to-face with an urban myth.

added.title: A King's Ransom
added.description: Ice King suffers a heartbreaking loss and it's up to Finn and Jake to find the culprit.

added.title: The Best VHS in the World
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to return an overdue VHS to the store so they won't be banned from renting new movies.

added.title: Prankless
added.description: The guys want to win a prank war with a rival park.

added.title: Fuzzy Dice
added.description: Everyone wants to give Pops some fuzzy dice for his birthday.

added.title: Sugar Rush
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to pick up the donuts for the morning meeting.

added.title: Bad Kiss
added.description: Mordecai finally makes his move and tries to kiss Margaret.

added.title: Public Radio
added.description: After listening to a public radio broadcast during class, Clarence is inspired to record a radio interview of his own featuring his buddy Sumo. When Ms. Baker hears the charming interview, she calls in a favor and gets Clarence a spot on the actual Aberdale Public Radio! The search is on - to find the perfect interview subject for his big day.

added.title: Cartoon Factory
added.description: Uncle Grandpa visits the cartoon factory to get some answers about his roots.

added.title: What's the Big Idea?
added.description: Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus try to help Uncle Grandpa get an idea.

added.title: Sunken Treasure
added.description: A relaxing beach day becomes an underwater adventure when Unikitty and her friends find a message in a bottle.

added.title: Dawn of the Donut
added.description: Dr. Fox's plans to deliver donuts all over the Unikingdom are sidetracked by Unikitty's reluctance to follow instructions.
